column5: I fished all day yesterday in the BBP area, walking many miles and drilling many holes. Worked from 125' to 75' looking for a fish willing to actually bite. As the skunk wore on into the afternoon I decided to play with the camera a bit, and set it on the snow to film myself drilling a hole...the only time I turned on the camera all day, and the only time I needed to.   Thanks for looking!
Great stuff! Really nice video. Thanks for the morning pick me up.
Wow, good timing on the video  Really nice fish there.  Awesome!!!!
Great stuff!! Wonderful when you luck out on videoing something at the right time....
Great video - good music matching too.
All I get is a white screen and takes me to your account.  Nice fish.
Not sure why, but I don't know much about photobucket.
Myself as well.this is a first.Just clicked on the auger screen and away it went.Just no arrow on this one.
Hmmm. Does this one do any better: http://s1223.beta.photobucket.com/user/fishinpixx/media/classic_zps89d81294.mp4.html
Great video. Retro looking and the audio was refreshing. Wish every hole I drilled was like that.
I guess the action wasn"t as hot as the day I met you out there but at least you got one. Great video and fish
Thanks guys...  Yeah thanks, and no, it was nothing like the day we were out there...
